        <h2 class="font-serif text-eai-navy">What the Institute Does</h2>

        <p>
          The Institute does six things (Figure 4). Each program has one job, one
          audience, and one measurable output. Together they form a complete operation —
          empirical record, applied analysis, recruitment, convening, distribution, and
          the long-form publication that anchors the rest. The Institute is built to do
          these six things and nothing else. The discipline of a short program list is
          part of how a small institution survives its first decade without drifting.
        </p>

        <figure class="my-10">
          <img
